{"id": 223725912, "title": "Train Services Continue Uninterrupted Despite Derailment On Abuja-Kaduna Route \u2014 NRC", "text": "The Nigerian Railway Corporation (NRC) has confirmed that normal passenger train services between its Rigasa Station in Kaduna and Idu in Abuja continued without disruption following a minor derailment on the route at Jere station on Sunday morning. In a statement signed by the NRC Deputy Director of Public Relations, Yakub Mahmood, the Corporation reassured the public that all passengers arrived safely at their destinations. \u201cNRC engineers are currently addressing the issue on-site. \u201cThe NRC apologises for any inconvenience and reiterates its commitment to passenger safety and comfort,\u201d the statement read. Earlier reports indicated that some coaches of a train, which departed from Rigasa Train Station in Kaduna to Abuja had derailed near the mountainous area of Jere in Kaduna State on Sunday. Sources stated that the train, carrying numerous passengers, left Kaduna at around 8am. Approximately an hour into the journey, three coaches derailed.", "summary": "The Nigerian Railway Corporation (NRC) has confirmed that normal passenger train services between its Rigasa Station in Kaduna and Idu in Abuja continued without disruption following a minor derailment on the route at Jere station on Sunday morning. In a statement signed by the NRC Deputy Director of Public Relations, Yakub Mahmood, the Corporation reassured [&#8230;]", "url": "https://leadership.ng/train-services-continue-uninterrupted-despite-derailment-on-abuja-kaduna-route-nrc/", "image": "https://leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/NRC-train.png", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 14:32:18", "author": "Orjime Moses", "authors": ["Orjime Moses"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ng", "sentiment": -0.167}